TY  - JOUR
T1  - Behind the Learning Curve: A Sketch of the Learning Process
AU  - Adler, Paul S.
AU  - Clark, Kim B.
Y1  - 1991/03/01
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.37.3.267
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.37.3.267
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 267
EP  - 281
VL  - 37
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This exploratory paper sketches some of the behavioral processes that give rise to the learning curve. Using data from two manufacturing departments in an electronic equipment company, we construct a model of productivity improvement as a function of cumulative output and two managerial variables?engineering changes and workforce training. Exploration of this model highlights the complex relationship between first-order and second-order learning.
AB  - This exploratory paper sketches some of the behavioral processes that give rise to the learning curve. Using data from two manufacturing departments in an electronic equipment company, we construct a model of productivity improvement as a function of cumulative output and two managerial variables?engineering changes and workforce training. Exploration of this model highlights the complex relationship between first-order and second-order learning.
