TY  - JOUR
T1  - On the Independence of Irrelevant Assets: McEntire's Conjecture
AU  - Deb, Raj
AU  - Hadar, Josef
AU  - Seo, Tae Kun
Y1  - 1991/03/01
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.37.3.301
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.37.3.301
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 301
EP  - 306
VL  - 37
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In his 1984 paper in Management Science, McEntire conjectured that all concave utility functions satisfy his independence-from-irrelevant-assets (IIA) property. This paper shows that this conjecture is false. The paper provides several families of utility functions, all of whose members violate the IIA property; moreover, it is shown that the set of utility functions violating the IIA property is quite large, and that it is widespread throughout the entire space of utility functions.
AB  - In his 1984 paper in Management Science, McEntire conjectured that all concave utility functions satisfy his independence-from-irrelevant-assets (IIA) property. This paper shows that this conjecture is false. The paper provides several families of utility functions, all of whose members violate the IIA property; moreover, it is shown that the set of utility functions violating the IIA property is quite large, and that it is widespread throughout the entire space of utility functions.
